Julie Davich: Could you speak about growing up in a collecting family? What=
 was that like?

=C2=A0

Adam Fields: It was amazing=E2=80=94not just to see the things being create=
d, but also to meet the people creating them. When my parents were
getting into collecting, Chicago had a lot of young artists, from Rashid Jo=
hnson to Angel Otero to Theaster Gates to Nick Cave. I was fortunate to mee=
t a lot of these people whom I can call friends, and it helped me to recogn=
ize my raison d=E2=80=99=C4=9Btre, if you will, which is that there wasn=E2=
=80=99t really an on-ramp to engage a younger generation in the art world. =
It=E2=80=99s an intimidating world that has a lot of gatekeepers. You need =
to
have relationships, means, and access. And obviously, it=E2=80=99s a very a=
ntiquated space. I took all of those things and said, =E2=80=9CWell, that=
=E2=80=99s how I want to engage.=E2=80=9D There are problems that the futur=
e generations of collectors and appreciators don=E2=80=99t want to deal wit=
h, so how can we try to change that?

When people talk about the market, they talk about it more from a value per=
spective, and less from a volume perspective. That=E2=80=99s something I=E2=
=80=99m trying
to change. The market is so much bigger. There=E2=80=99s such a volume of i=
tems=E2=80=94whether it=E2=80=99s art, collectibles, luxury items=E2=80=94t=
hat people have a deep interest in. Seeing the breadth and range of people=
=E2=80=99s interests has been eye-opening.

Do you collect?

=C2=A0

Definitely, but it=E2=80=99s been a while since I=E2=80=99ve bought anythin=
g new, for space and budget
reasons with a young family. My collection started with pieces from the Chi=
cago artists I knew and loved growing up=E2=80=94Johnson, Otero, Tony Lewis=
, Rob Davis, William J. O=E2=80=99Brien=E2=80=94and expanded into younger a=
rtists on the ascent that I was able to get into, from a price perspective,=
 before they got out of my range, like Richard Aldrich, Ella Kruglyanskaya,=
 Raphaela Simon, and Satoshi
Kojima.

