in-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>=
<em>Julie Davich: </em></strong><strong>Could you speak about growing up in=
 a collecting family? What was that like?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>=
Adam Fields</em>: It was amazing=E2=80=94not just to see the things being c=
reated, but also to meet the people creating them. When my parents were
getting into collecting, Chicago had a lot of young artists, from <strong>R=
ashid Johnson</strong> to <strong>Angel Otero</strong> to <strong>Theaster =
Gates</strong> to <strong>Nick Cave</strong>. I was fortunate to meet a lot=
 of these people whom I can call friends, and it helped me to recognize my =
<em>raison d=E2=80=99=C4=9Btre</em>, if you will, which is that there wasn=
=E2=80=99t really an on-ramp to engage a younger generation in the art worl=
d. It=E2=80=99s an intimidating world that has a lot of gatekeepers. You ne=
ed to
have relationships, means, and access. And obviously, it=E2=80=99s a very a=
ntiquated space. I took all of those things and said, =E2=80=9CWell, that=
=E2=80=99s how I want to engage.=E2=80=9D There are problems that the futur=
e generations of collectors and appreciators don=E2=80=99t want to deal wit=
h, so how can we try to change that?</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;"><br/>When people talk about the market, they talk about it more from =
a <em>value</em> perspective, and less from a volume perspective. That=E2=
=80=99s something I=E2=80=99m trying
to change. The market is so much <em>bigger</em>. There=E2=80=99s such a vo=
lume of items=E2=80=94whether it=E2=80=99s art, collectibles, luxury items=
=E2=80=94that people have a deep interest in. Seeing the breadth and range =
of people=E2=80=99s interests has been eye-opening.<br/><br/></p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Do you collect?</strong></p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">Definitely, but it=E2=80=99s been a while since I=E2=80=99ve bou=
ght anything new, for space and budget
reasons with a young family. My collection started with pieces from the Chi=
cago artists I knew and loved growing up=E2=80=94Johnson, Otero, <strong>To=
ny Lewis</strong>, <strong>Rob Davis</strong>, <strong>William J. O=E2=80=
=99Brien</strong>=E2=80=94and expanded into younger artists on the ascent t=
hat I was able to get into, from a price perspective, before they got out o=
f my range, like <strong>Richard Aldrich</strong>, <strong>Ella Kruglyanska=
ya</strong>, <strong>Raphaela Simon</strong>, and <strong>Satoshi
Kojima</strong>.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>[<a href=3D"https://email.p=
