are-foot, early 20th century, Neo-Renaissance mansion, which sits across th=
e street from the Guggenheim. Naturally, the immensely photogenic, <strong>=
Rafael Vi=C3=B1oly</strong>=E2=80=93renovated space has been trending on Ti=
kTok lately.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>Indeed, Salon 94 gets up =
to <em>2,000 visitors</em> every Saturday. Marion told me he had to take th=
e elevator last weekend because two wannabe influencers were
perched on the oval stairway waiting for the photographer they=E2=80=99d hi=
red. When I was there, another influencer was posing alongside Japanese cer=
amicist <strong>Takuro Kuwata</strong>=E2=80=99s meditative rock garden, wh=
ich is carefully arranged with his large, brightly colored sculptures.</p><=
